title: City Reform
new-page: true
is-card: true
tags: city
on-arrival: month_actions += 1;
card-image: img/sangerbund.jpg

- @gerrymandering: We need to reform the electoral system.
- @city_reform_doi: We need to reform the department of investigation.

@gerrymandering

While the american system naturally trends towards a certain impossible to limit level of corruption and inequality, the deck of Gotham city is so crooked the top card is getting dusty. While profound reform of the city will be the hardest to implement, they are also the most important.

The map of council districts inside of the city is profoundly gerrymandered. This ought to change.

The current map heavily favors white voters over minorities, packing and cracking communities allowing the republican party to maintain majorities even when the city wide election doesn't go their way. Yet, by that matter, it became a deeply partisan issue.

(Show breakdown of seats per population of the current map)

To change the map, you will require an absolute majority vote of the very same councilor that stand to run for them every 2 years. Here are the following potential plans:

- @fair_map: We need a fair map, nothing more, nothing less.
- @democrat_gerrymandering: For decades, this city as favored unjustly one party over the other. One party that has brought this city to the brink multiple time. It's now time for the council to do away with those reactionaries.
- @bruce_gerrymandering: I think there is a part of the city that is willing to bring change, but the other simply is not ready for it. We need to bring about drastic changes. The city seats should reflect those that trully want to bring out change more than those that won't.

@fair_map
subtitle: While difficult, you possess two avenues to reach it, either through the court or through the city. If passed, it will see the council finally be represent it's actual population.

(Show breakdown of seats per population of the fair map)

- @city_reform_court: We will go through the court. We will make clear that the current map as a Racially based gerrymandering. The excuse of it being done by wealth can only go so far when a city with a third of it's population being from minority groups only has 13% of it's councilors from such communities.
- @city_reform_city_council: We will go through the hardest point, through the city council. It will require all strength to achieve it, but it's our ticket for change in this city.

@city_reform_court
