subtitle: Going through the court may take years. However, it is nearly guaranteed that the case will eventually be passed thanks to overwhelming evidence. Still, you will need to stack the deck in your favor to see it come sooner rather than later. Furthermore, for as long as it last, your polling and credibility will be put to the test. 

@city_reform_city_council
subtitle: To achieve it you will need the support of 43 out of 65 councilors. achieving it will require incredibly strong support or very deep pockets. 


@democrat_gerrymandering
choose-if: moral_compass < 25
subtitle: Gerrymandering the map the other way is certain to guarantee democratic control for decades to come. However, are we really going to cook the book to defeat those that cooked it in the past? In any case, it would require 43 out of 65 councilor to manage it. Furthermore, we may be spending a year against litigation to have it finally succeed.

@bruce_gerrymandering
subtitle: Gerrymandering the council map to support groups that support you is seen as the most corrupt breach of conduct and attempt of taking power anyone could describe. You will need an incredible amount of support to make it past the 43 seat required as both establishment democrats and republicans will act against it. We won't be able to pass it until a year after it is done.

@city_reform_doi

The current head of the department of investigation, Arnold Flass, is known to be corrupt and to help his crooks inside the council. However, Rupert Thorne and his crooks would lock up the council if you dare to strike their man without reason. If you do have them, it opens the door both to judicial investigation and further reform eliminating corruption from future candidate.

- @doi_vote: Let's undergo a substantial reform of the department. There is so much things wrong only a full and complete change of the guard can be enough to bring back a sense of normality.
- @arnold_flass: Let's try to remove the main culprit. Arnold Flass represent everything that is wrong in the governmental structure of Gotham, perhaps even more than Thorne. He needs to go.


@doi_vote
choose-if: rupert_advisor == 0
subtitle: Needs a simple majority vote. Corrupt councilors will always vote no no matter how much you pay them.

@arnold_flass
subtitle: Thorne is ready to give you those token reforms. In would however ask you to give him something in exchange.

- @bribe_thorne: Thorne can be bought by anyone with enough money, let him say his price, i'll pay it.
- @thorne_support: We've worked together previously, I'm certain he can let it go for this one that is just bringing heat onto us.

@bribe_thorne
subtitle: At the cost of a substantial amount of PF's, he will abandon his stooge.

@thorne_support